<br />
7. Always pick a dueling location where you can abuse the territory.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That is a very stupid cleric if they are allowing you to do that.
<br />

<br />
A half way skilled cleric will not allow you to do any of the above. You are kidding yourself if you truly think that will work.
<br />

<br />
1. Cleric cast's a HoT on himslef for added security.
<br />
2. Stun mage.
<br />
3. Root pet.
<br />
4. Dispell mage.
<br />
5. Clicky hammer pet.(TGT mage..pet is worthless except it does interupt casteing)
<br />
6. RE root pet if needed.
<br />
7. MoK mage and pet...Clicky MoR mage and Pet.
<br />
8. Melee mage to death, refreshing HoT, or root if needed.
<br />

<br />
That is a very stupid cleric if they are allowing you to do that.
<br />

<br />
A half way skilled cleric will not allow you to do any of the above. You are kidding yourself if you truly think that will work.
<br />

<br />
1. Cleric cast's a HoT on himself for added security.
<br />
2. Stun, blind mage.
<br />
3. Root pet.
<br />
4. Dispell mage.
<br />
5. Clicky hammer pet. (TGT mage. pet is worthless except it does interrupt casting)
<br />
6. RE root pet if needed. stun, blind mage.
<br />
7. MoK mage and pet...Clicky MoR mage and Pet.
<br />
8. Melee mage to death, refreshing HoT, or root if needed.
<br />

<br />
The possible flaws in the above.
<br />
Mage manages to get off HoE, and send in pet before I get him stunned. I will use one of my DA’s, which with AA's and Focus last about 30 seconds. And just stand there and wait for the HoE to Poof. If DA drops before HoE is over, use AA HoT which will out-heal their damage for the few seconds remaining, plus gives me the added security measure I said above. 
<br />

<br />
If mage manages to dispell root, or root breaks while I am beating on mage. Then re-root pet, back out of melee range and use knock back stuns on mage to pull him to within melee range but out of pet range, and root mage and continue beating him to death, between bash, DD proc, hammer pet, and knock back stuns it will be very hard for the mage to manage to cast any spells. If he manages to channel a nuke, it isn’t going to do much for him. With FT, self buffs, and yaulp I can self heal for days.
<br />
What it comes down to is simple. Your pet is the only way your going to beat a cleric. I am not going to write what if to every possible situation I will just hit a couple of highlights. 
<br />
First the cleric is going to stun, and try to blind you before dealing with the pet. He isn’t going to focus on the pet first and give you a chance to dispel him so he has to start the clicky vs. dispell game. Once you are stun, it gives me enough time to deal with pet. The cleric isn’t going to try to nuke you until you get low on health, I will save my mana for heals, stuns. If blind lands then I know I can use nukes as the finishing blow, if stuns and blinds both are resisted then I am not going to bother trying to nuke you. However even if the stuns are resisted, the knock back portion will still work, so I can use them to position you and interrupt casting between them and bashing. The cleric pet is immune to spell unless the spell is Unresistable. So it is handy to use to interrupt casters. And since you said that cleric was elemental, he will have, clicky hammer pet, clicky MoR. If you try to abuse the territory and run, etc. I am not going to chase you down. I will just wait till root breaks on pet then run it in the opposite direction you ran, and root it when you try to call it back. And then move to you. Since you can't root Poofy the hammer, I can use him to track you. If you stop to deal with poofy after I have your pet out of the way then a stun should be good enough to allow me to close within melee range. And once I get within melee range your dead. The cleric hammer proc is unresistable, and with melee DPS, bash DPS added their isn’t anything you can really do without your pet. You can try to shadow step but it won’t give you enough range away from me to matter. Ok this post is already way to long, so I will end with this. Given the right conditions and ideal situations any class can beat another. PvP is mainly about waiting until the other person is already weak so you can take advantage. Both sides being equal, depends on the person behind the toon, but if you think that you can beat a cleric easily, and with tactics like stated above, then you are going to be getting a free trip to your bind point.
<br />

<br />
*Note: Feel free to post another "tactics" you have in mind and I will tell you the clerics reaction to it.<br />_________________<br /><span style="color: blue"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=770163" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jaffo</a></span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
