			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Clerics LOVE to blind you.  Be ready for it.  Buy a bio orb and blind them first $$
<br />

<br />
Have a silverflank belt or clicky belt from veksar?
<br />

<br />
the silverflank is optimal for this, on a rooted pet, run up next to the cleric and summon companion clicky your pet on top of them.  Always ruffles feathers.
<br />

<br />
I do all my fighting in the arena in lake rathe so environment is something I can't really comment on.
<br />

<br />
Pumice stones that are vendor bought.  Get some.  You can also summon a 1 charge dispel staff.  Have it with you.
<br />

<br />
Being able to bind yourself somewhere near the action is always nice if the cleric doesn't see you do it.  Gating doesn't smoke your pet so you can have an escape route if needed.
<br />

<br />
ts very tough to wear clerics down if they are smart with their mana.  Harrass them with your pet as much as possible, its your only key.
<br />

<br />
Unless you get uber lucky and burn the fucker down!<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=560292" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.sinensis.org/images/eq/way1.jpg" border="0" /></a><a href="http://www.tribalfury.org" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.sinensis.org/images/eq/way2.jpg" border="0" /></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=523387" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.sinensis.org/images/eq/way3.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
