			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Jaffo wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If mage manages to dispell root, or root breaks while I am beating on mage. Then re-root pet, back out of melee range and use knock back stuns on mage to pull him to within melee range but out of pet range, and root mage and continue beating him to death, between bash, DD proc, hammer pet, and knock back stuns it will be very hard for the mage to manage to cast any spells. If he manages to channel a nuke, it isn’t going to do much for him. With FT, self buffs, and yaulp I can self heal for days. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
not sure what server u play on jaffo, but on vz knockback does not work in pvp... the stun effect might work, but the knockback doesnt... which brings me to another thing... i only have 291mr unbuffed, by far not the highest on my server, and i cannot remember the last time i was stunned/blinded, even after tash/malos.
<br />

<br />
As for my strategy against clerics, to be honest sometimes i dont even bother, because they really can heal forever, which does 100% in pvp and is not effected by resists.  fighting a cleric is kind of like fighting a druid, its like a game of chess, u do a move, they do a move, u do a move.... anywho when fighting a cleric u gotta kno that cleric's strat, some clerics jus chase u wit hahmmer and conserve mana only for heals, some nuke, some use a combo of both. to kill a clr you have to somehow surprise him, whether it be making him think u're burning all u're mana so he uses all his up healing, pretending u're lom so he gets careless and nukes, whatever u're sneaky mind can think of, but bottom line is in the end, u cannot wear him down unless u have a pillage bracer, so only way u'll win is if he allows himself to drop under 70%, then burn him hard, hope for some lucky crits + hope u're pet interrupts his heals... he'll prolly DA if he can if u get him real low, jus sit with u're pet atkin him until DA wears off and continue the burn.
<br />

<br />
if you have a pillage bracer, i doubt u need my advice on how to kill a cleric.
<br />

<br />
if you have decent regen, and if you can keep u're DS up (shouldnt be hard with clickies and decent MR) then jus let his pet hit u if he summons it, it should die after hitting u like 3 times... if not, back u're pet off and tell it to atk the pet, it should 1 round the pet then go right for the cleric again.
<br />

<br />
if you played your cards wrong and the cleric ran u oom, gate.
<br />

<br />
if you're better gear'd than the clr u're fighting, use Nullify magic alot, dispell any debuffs he puts on u're pet, and keep nullifying him for a good 2-5 mins, even if he keeps using clickies. it can jump buffslots sometimes, and hope u get his virtue/c3/anythinggood.  this does 3 things.  first, it allows u to wear him down easier by lowering his manaregen, ac (gogo pet), and heal efficiency (if he has to use a 2k heal to heal 1k dmg because its 40% of his life, he's not as efficient). second, sometimes after you get all their buffs they'll stop using their clickies, or only use 1 or 2 after each dispell, so u kno they're pretty much buffless. the main advantage of this is they can no longer use their heal over times, and if they do u can jus dispell it, and they'll end up losing lots of mana. third and last, if that cleric gates or zones, even if u didnt get the kill he'll be oom and buffless, so u dont have to worry about him for a while.
<br />

<br />
last but not least, regen or shield of auras helps, or both, because he can heal, u cannot, so its a lot easier for him to wear u down, since u can be 90m but if u're at 10%hp that mana isnt gonna help u, so clicky rune, heal potions, and regen are the only heals u're gonna get.
<br />

<br />
last but not least, dont die to a cleric or u're friends will laugh at you.<br />_________________<br />Meetmefrend
<br />

<br />
Magician of Zephyros, Vallon Zek</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
